South Africa Starts Audit of Mining Rights Holders, Business Report Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-02-14T05:18:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/s-africa-starts-audit-of-mining-rights-holders-bus-report-says.html
  South Africa ’s mineral resources
department started auditing all mining rights holders to
establish if they are honoring conditions of their mining
rights,  Business Report  said, citing Bheki Khumalo, the
department’s spokesman.  Khumalo didn’t say how many rights holders will be
investigated or how far the probe will go back, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
